1
00:02:06,304 --> 00:02:08,344
Can you take me to see him?

2
00:02:09,265 --> 00:02:10,825
I have to ask him something.

3
00:02:10,904 --> 00:02:14,385
Tarn told me
that he wanted Nut to be happy.

4
00:02:14,464 --> 00:02:16,065
He wants him to do the job he loves

5
00:02:16,665 --> 00:02:18,705
and be surrounded by good people.

6
00:02:18,785 --> 00:02:20,825
…You meet someone better than me,

7
00:02:21,624 --> 00:02:24,025
someone you are happier with,

8
00:02:24,105 --> 00:02:26,064
and isn't a burden like me?

9
00:02:28,025 --> 00:02:29,385
Will you leave me for him?

10
00:02:29,464 --> 00:02:31,064
Did you bring me here

11
00:02:32,265 --> 00:02:33,464
for a particular reason?

12
00:02:33,545 --> 00:02:35,705
Each of us is a unique flower.

13
00:02:35,785 --> 00:02:37,904
You are a special flower

14
00:02:37,985 --> 00:02:39,064
that belongs to me.

15
00:02:42,184 --> 00:02:43,265
Tofu.

16
00:02:48,705 --> 00:02:50,624
I'm glad I get to love you.

17
00:03:00,265 --> 00:03:01,784
If death parts us one day

18
00:03:03,425 --> 00:03:05,624
and a miracle brings us back together,

19
00:03:08,825 --> 00:03:10,624
would we fall in love again?

20
00:03:15,064 --> 00:03:16,865
If I died

21
00:03:18,585 --> 00:03:20,145
and came back as a ghost,

22
00:03:21,425 --> 00:03:22,504
would you run from me?

23
00:03:26,265 --> 00:03:28,145
I wouldn't run even if you were ugly.

24
00:03:28,904 --> 00:03:30,105
I see.

25
00:03:30,184 --> 00:03:31,825
I should come back all handsome,

26
00:03:33,305 --> 00:03:34,904
so you would fall for me first.

27
00:03:42,665 --> 00:03:43,865
Is something wrong, Nut?

28
00:03:46,945 --> 00:03:47,945
I'm fine.

29
00:03:50,064 --> 00:03:51,385
To me,

30
00:03:52,665 --> 00:03:54,064
the fact that we are together

31
00:03:54,865 --> 00:03:55,985
is a dream come true.

32
00:03:57,825 --> 00:03:59,585
Luck doesn't come by often.

33
00:04:03,784 --> 00:04:05,145
You are being too modest.

34
00:04:06,224 --> 00:04:07,665
I'm being ambitious.

35
00:04:10,665 --> 00:04:12,344
I just don't want us to part ways.

36
00:04:23,824 --> 00:04:24,704
What are you doing?

37
00:04:25,264 --> 00:04:26,905
Well, I'm taking a photo as proof.

38
00:04:27,385 --> 00:04:29,505
You promised to love me and only me.

39
00:04:30,945 --> 00:04:31,865
Stop it.

40
00:04:33,905 --> 00:04:35,025
Stop it, Tarn.

41
00:04:59,385 --> 00:05:00,625
I'm sorry, Nut.

42
00:05:04,305 --> 00:05:05,905
I didn't know how to tell you.

43
00:05:18,824 --> 00:05:20,225
The person you recognized…

44
00:05:23,345 --> 00:05:24,704
Was it really Tarn?

45
00:05:27,425 --> 00:05:28,425
Yes.

46
00:05:34,745 --> 00:05:35,905
I just found out

47
00:05:36,425 --> 00:05:38,024
that Prib knows him too.

48
00:05:40,264 --> 00:05:42,065
We came here together yesterday.

49
00:05:44,345 --> 00:05:45,305
Yesterday?

50
00:05:49,905 --> 00:05:51,185
You recognized Tarn.

51
00:05:53,024 --> 00:05:54,505
You knew who he was.

52
00:05:56,945 --> 00:05:58,545
Why didn't you tell me?

53
00:06:01,625 --> 00:06:03,985
And you still asked me those questions.

54
00:06:16,785 --> 00:06:17,745
You know,

55
00:06:19,144 --> 00:06:21,425
I wasn't delighted at all when you said

56
00:06:23,345 --> 00:06:24,704
you recognized him.

57
00:06:29,185 --> 00:06:30,144
I was scared.

58
00:06:35,264 --> 00:06:37,505
I was scared that if I brought you to him,

59
00:06:39,625 --> 00:06:41,065
I would lose you.

60
00:06:47,024 --> 00:06:48,264
But if I held you back,

61
00:06:51,185 --> 00:06:52,264
you would be hurt.

62
00:07:06,865 --> 00:07:08,225
I'm sorry.

63
00:07:13,024 --> 00:07:14,865
I hurt your feelings again.

64
00:07:18,505 --> 00:07:19,945
I'm really sorry.

65
00:07:26,625 --> 00:07:28,144
You didn't hurt me.

66
00:07:34,144 --> 00:07:35,425
I was just surprised.

67
00:07:40,264 --> 00:07:41,824
I thought of him…

68
00:07:45,344 --> 00:07:47,545
but I didn't expect to see him
in that condition.

69
00:07:53,105 --> 00:07:54,425
I didn't think

70
00:07:56,904 --> 00:07:58,024
that you guys…

71
00:08:04,105 --> 00:08:05,305
would know each other.

72
00:08:13,264 --> 00:08:14,704
Aren't you happy

73
00:08:16,105 --> 00:08:17,344
to see him again?

74
00:08:25,024 --> 00:08:25,985
I never thought

75
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:28,824
about how I would feel
if I ever saw him again.

76
00:08:33,264 --> 00:08:34,424
But just now,

77
00:08:36,865 --> 00:08:38,144
when I saw him…

78
00:08:46,064 --> 00:08:47,705
I realized that he wasn't just…

79
00:08:52,225 --> 00:08:53,145
Just on your mind.

80
00:08:56,625 --> 00:08:57,705
You miss him.

81
00:09:04,025 --> 00:09:06,025
Do you still love Tatarn?

82
00:09:13,225 --> 00:09:14,345
I don't know.

83
00:09:22,304 --> 00:09:23,985
But I really love you, Tofu.

84
00:09:35,465 --> 00:09:36,345
Thank you.

85
00:09:50,145 --> 00:09:51,585
It's really funny.

86
00:09:55,064 --> 00:09:56,905
How can the two people I love

87
00:09:58,745 --> 00:09:59,944
know each other?

88
00:10:04,424 --> 00:10:06,745
Why did you have to see Tarn?

89
00:10:10,905 --> 00:10:12,905
Why do you know each other?

90
00:10:42,025 --> 00:10:44,184
AN OLD STORY RETOLD…
AFTER A LONG WHILE

91
00:10:53,745 --> 00:10:55,824
Tofu told you all about it, didn't he?

92
00:11:01,625 --> 00:11:02,944
I'm sorry

93
00:11:04,265 --> 00:11:07,345
for causing trouble
and hurting your and Tofu's feelings.

94
00:11:10,865 --> 00:11:13,465
I don't know if a miracle
will happen or not.

95
00:11:14,944 --> 00:11:16,184
All I can do is hope.

96
00:11:17,465 --> 00:11:18,905
If a miracle happens,

97
00:11:19,944 --> 00:11:21,225
that would be good.

98
00:11:25,145 --> 00:11:26,265
But if it doesn't…

99
00:11:47,184 --> 00:11:49,184
Do you still love Tatarn?

100
00:11:52,905 --> 00:11:53,985
I don't know.

101
00:11:56,385 --> 00:11:58,225
But I really love you, Tofu.

102
00:12:23,025 --> 00:12:24,025
Don't worry about it.

103
00:12:24,985 --> 00:12:26,745
They used to date after all.

104
00:12:26,824 --> 00:12:28,345
Nut is just showing his support.

105
00:12:34,345 --> 00:12:35,345
Mr. Saen.

106
00:12:35,944 --> 00:12:36,824
Jan.

107
00:12:55,625 --> 00:12:58,304
I can't believe we all know each other.

108
00:12:59,385 --> 00:13:01,064
People say it's a small world.

109
00:13:01,145 --> 00:13:02,585
Everyone is family.

110
00:13:02,665 --> 00:13:04,704
We are either related by blood

111
00:13:05,345 --> 00:13:06,265
or by sex.

112
00:13:07,704 --> 00:13:09,585
Stay quiet if you have nothing to say.

113
00:13:09,665 --> 00:13:11,905
I was just making a joke.

114
00:13:13,704 --> 00:13:15,385
You came all this way to make a joke.

115
00:13:15,465 --> 00:13:17,505
You must have a lot of time on your hands.

116
00:13:18,064 --> 00:13:19,665
Yes, I do.

117
00:13:20,225 --> 00:13:22,824
I went to see Saen
after I collected the rent.

118
00:13:24,145 --> 00:13:26,225
If I had known
you wanted to join our trip,

119
00:13:26,824 --> 00:13:28,145
I would have invited you.

120
00:13:29,505 --> 00:13:32,424
A trip with me wouldn't be as fun
as a trip with your gay…

121
00:13:33,385 --> 00:13:36,225
I mean, your family.

122
00:13:36,865 --> 00:13:39,025
Na must be really happy

123
00:13:39,105 --> 00:13:40,665
that her son

124
00:13:41,225 --> 00:13:43,304
and his friend took her on a trip.

125
00:13:44,665 --> 00:13:45,585
Yes.

126
00:13:46,505 --> 00:13:48,585
I was going to visit you with my mom.

127
00:13:49,225 --> 00:13:51,304
You didn't have much time
to talk last time.

128
00:13:51,865 --> 00:13:54,184
You guys get along really well.

129
00:13:54,265 --> 00:13:55,704
She would be happy to see you.

130
00:13:56,745 --> 00:13:57,704
Right, Tofu?

131
00:13:59,824 --> 00:14:00,704
Yes.

132
00:14:03,105 --> 00:14:05,704
Why don't you invite Na over for dinner?

133
00:14:05,785 --> 00:14:08,025
-We can have a long conversation.
-No.

134
00:14:08,824 --> 00:14:10,785
I'm sure their schedule is packed.

135
00:14:11,345 --> 00:14:13,704
Why not? Are you afraid of something?

136
00:14:14,304 --> 00:14:16,505
Don't you want to see an old friend?

137
00:14:17,745 --> 00:14:18,865
Sure.

138
00:14:20,704 --> 00:14:22,704
It has been a while
since we ate as a family.

139
00:14:35,985 --> 00:14:37,865
If you and Tofu hadn't visited Tarn,

140
00:14:37,944 --> 00:14:40,824
we wouldn't be having
a meal together like this.

141
00:14:44,745 --> 00:14:46,145
Did you say Tarn?

142
00:14:49,145 --> 00:14:50,905
Tarn, the guy Tofu recognized,

143
00:14:51,424 --> 00:14:52,665
is Jan's nephew.

144
00:14:54,745 --> 00:14:57,465
I don't know how close Tarn and Tofu were.

145
00:14:58,064 --> 00:14:58,985
I hope

146
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:00,785
it is not what I think it is.

147
00:15:09,865 --> 00:15:10,785
Everyone.

148
00:15:10,865 --> 00:15:12,265
The food is here.

149
00:15:12,345 --> 00:15:14,584
Let's all eat.

150
00:15:14,665 --> 00:15:16,304
The food here is great.

151
00:15:16,385 --> 00:15:17,865
My dad takes me here often.

152
00:15:19,385 --> 00:15:20,865
Jan, do you happen to know

153
00:15:22,505 --> 00:15:23,865
how close

154
00:15:25,385 --> 00:15:26,704
Tarn and I were?

155
00:15:32,665 --> 00:15:34,225
I don't know.

156
00:15:35,064 --> 00:15:36,865
If I had known you,

157
00:15:36,944 --> 00:15:39,184
I would have recognized you
from the beginning.

158
00:15:39,265 --> 00:15:42,465
Tarn's mouth often got him in trouble,

159
00:15:42,544 --> 00:15:43,944
so we weren't really close.

160
00:15:44,544 --> 00:15:45,665
All I remember is

161
00:15:45,745 --> 00:15:48,145
when he was in high school in Bangkok,

162
00:15:48,225 --> 00:15:50,865
he got called into the principal's office.

163
00:15:51,505 --> 00:15:54,584
I don't know what happened back then.

164
00:15:54,665 --> 00:15:56,105
But I kind of

165
00:15:56,184 --> 00:15:57,225
have an idea now.

166
00:15:59,064 --> 00:16:01,265
I wonder whose toes
he stepped on this time.

167
00:16:01,345 --> 00:16:02,704
That person put him in a coma.

168
00:16:04,665 --> 00:16:06,824
We'll have to wait for him to wake up

169
00:16:07,464 --> 00:16:09,345
to find out whose toes he stepped on.

170
00:16:12,265 --> 00:16:13,584
Tarn wouldn't get involved

171
00:16:14,865 --> 00:16:16,105
for no reason.

172
00:16:17,625 --> 00:16:19,985
You seem to know a lot about him.

173
00:16:20,064 --> 00:16:21,424
You must have been close.

174
00:16:22,544 --> 00:16:24,424
If that's true,

175
00:16:24,505 --> 00:16:26,584
I hope someone here doesn't mind.

176
00:16:28,265 --> 00:16:29,944
It's none of your business.

177
00:16:30,665 --> 00:16:31,745
Just eat.

178
00:16:34,985 --> 00:16:36,865
Tarn and I used to be close.

179
00:16:38,824 --> 00:16:40,505
We were a couple.

180
00:16:49,064 --> 00:16:49,985
But right now,

181
00:16:50,785 --> 00:16:51,985
Tofu and I

182
00:16:52,785 --> 00:16:53,865
are a couple.

183
00:16:56,505 --> 00:16:57,905
You finally came out.

184
00:17:01,505 --> 00:17:04,105
Actually, I don't feel
the need to announce

185
00:17:04,184 --> 00:17:05,345
what I am

186
00:17:05,424 --> 00:17:06,545
and who I'm dating.

187
00:17:07,665 --> 00:17:09,105
But if you really want to know,

188
00:17:09,665 --> 00:17:10,545
I can tell you.

189
00:17:12,504 --> 00:17:14,504
It's not something
to be embarrassed about.

190
00:17:15,984 --> 00:17:17,944
We are just like a heterosexual couple.

191
00:17:19,224 --> 00:17:20,424
We live in the same house,

192
00:17:21,024 --> 00:17:22,105
spend time together,

193
00:17:23,224 --> 00:17:24,305
and sleep together.

194
00:17:26,825 --> 00:17:28,705
I think it's more embarrassing

195
00:17:29,425 --> 00:17:31,305
to pretend to have a perfect relationship

196
00:17:33,225 --> 00:17:34,825
when it's far from the truth.

197
00:17:38,465 --> 00:17:39,785
I'm surprised

198
00:17:39,865 --> 00:17:41,705
at how honest you're being.

199
00:17:44,225 --> 00:17:45,905
The fact that you're okay with this

200
00:17:45,984 --> 00:17:48,024
proves you are quite ignorant.

201
00:17:50,264 --> 00:17:52,345
That's not true.

202
00:17:52,905 --> 00:17:53,825
The ignorant one

203
00:17:54,625 --> 00:17:56,385
is the person judging other people.

204
00:17:56,465 --> 00:17:59,145
Is it wrong that some people
can't accept it?

205
00:17:59,225 --> 00:18:00,545
No, it's not.

206
00:18:01,425 --> 00:18:03,185
Whether someone can accept it or not,

207
00:18:03,264 --> 00:18:04,225
it's their problem.

208
00:18:05,105 --> 00:18:06,024
Everyone has rights.

209
00:18:07,345 --> 00:18:08,625
I just realized

210
00:18:08,705 --> 00:18:10,345
that you're not just a screenwriter,

211
00:18:10,425 --> 00:18:12,665
but you are a human rights activist too.

212
00:18:14,385 --> 00:18:16,705
Anyone can show interest in human rights.

213
00:18:16,785 --> 00:18:18,825
It's up to us whether we care or not.

214
00:18:19,825 --> 00:18:23,185
People have been paying attention

215
00:18:23,264 --> 00:18:24,984
to human rights and equality.

216
00:18:25,825 --> 00:18:28,065
You don't have to be an LGBTQ+

217
00:18:28,145 --> 00:18:31,625
in order to fight for their rights.

218
00:18:32,305 --> 00:18:34,385
You don't have to be a disabled person

219
00:18:34,465 --> 00:18:37,145
in order to fight for their rights.

220
00:18:38,225 --> 00:18:39,465
Your voice

221
00:18:39,545 --> 00:18:40,984
can help other people.

222
00:18:41,984 --> 00:18:45,784
I understand you need principle and reason
to talk to kids these days.

223
00:18:45,865 --> 00:18:47,744
I might be old-fashioned,

224
00:18:47,825 --> 00:18:50,145
but I will try to understand
your point of view.

225
00:18:50,665 --> 00:18:51,905
People from my days

226
00:18:51,984 --> 00:18:55,264
would call you guys "faggots,"

227
00:18:56,065 --> 00:18:58,225
but people nowadays would probably say

228
00:18:58,705 --> 00:19:00,625
you are just two people in love.

229
00:19:00,705 --> 00:19:01,625
A genderless love.

230
00:19:01,705 --> 00:19:03,784
Something like that, right?

231
00:19:05,705 --> 00:19:07,585
Everybody has a gender.

232
00:19:08,105 --> 00:19:10,225
You can be any gender you wish to be.

233
00:19:10,865 --> 00:19:13,264
And every gender is equal.

234
00:19:14,345 --> 00:19:16,665
The term "genderless love"

235
00:19:16,744 --> 00:19:18,744
might sound romantic to you,

236
00:19:19,385 --> 00:19:23,305
but it shows how
you do not accept our identities.

237
00:19:25,145 --> 00:19:26,665
Specifying one's gender

238
00:19:26,744 --> 00:19:29,105
is a way to show respect.

239
00:19:32,185 --> 00:19:34,065
If you still don't get it,

240
00:19:34,145 --> 00:19:36,065
I would be happy to explain it

241
00:19:36,145 --> 00:19:37,145
when you are free.

242
00:19:37,825 --> 00:19:39,185
There are many things

243
00:19:39,264 --> 00:19:41,185
we need to discuss.

244
00:19:41,264 --> 00:19:42,345
Got it?

245
00:19:43,425 --> 00:19:44,264
Sajjaree.

246
00:19:44,825 --> 00:19:46,225
Stop it, Jan.

247
00:19:48,665 --> 00:19:49,865
-What?
-Come with me.

248
00:19:50,385 --> 00:19:51,305
What is it?

249
00:20:00,425 --> 00:20:01,665
I'm going to the toilet.

250
00:20:03,744 --> 00:20:05,425
I'll go with you.

251
00:20:06,185 --> 00:20:07,024
It's okay.

252
00:20:07,625 --> 00:20:09,744
I can go alone. Please enjoy the meal.

253
00:20:26,264 --> 00:20:27,585
This family gathering

254
00:20:28,065 --> 00:20:29,585
is so damn heartwarming.

255
00:20:38,305 --> 00:20:40,425
What is it? Let me go.

256
00:20:40,504 --> 00:20:41,504
Stop it.

257
00:20:44,504 --> 00:20:45,784
-Listen.
-Let go.

258
00:20:45,865 --> 00:20:47,465
Why did you do that?

259
00:20:47,545 --> 00:20:49,065
Do what?

260
00:20:49,145 --> 00:20:51,264
You asked Nut about his personal life

261
00:20:51,345 --> 00:20:52,705
and made him uncomfortable.

262
00:20:53,345 --> 00:20:54,905
What good did it do?

263
00:20:54,984 --> 00:20:56,705
Did it make your life better?

264
00:20:56,784 --> 00:20:59,665
-They were rude to me first.
-Stop it.

265
00:20:59,744 --> 00:21:01,105
Don't be silly.

266
00:21:01,185 --> 00:21:04,065
You invited them to scold you.

267
00:21:04,145 --> 00:21:05,825
-So why are you upset?
-Saen.

268
00:21:05,905 --> 00:21:08,425
Do you think I don't know why you're here?

269
00:21:08,504 --> 00:21:11,625
Enough with the stupid jealousy.

270
00:21:11,705 --> 00:21:12,784
It's embarrassing.

271
00:21:14,305 --> 00:21:16,145
If you can't do it for your sake,

272
00:21:16,225 --> 00:21:18,905
then do it for the sake
of your so-called husband.

273
00:21:37,385 --> 00:21:38,345
Aren't you hungry?

274
00:21:38,945 --> 00:21:40,305
You keep staring at the food.

275
00:21:41,865 --> 00:21:44,385
We are at a very famous restaurant.

276
00:21:44,465 --> 00:21:46,425
We can't just sit here.

277
00:21:46,984 --> 00:21:48,625
All right, I'll start the meal.

278
00:21:49,905 --> 00:21:51,225
You guys go ahead and eat.

