00:45:36,265 --> 00:45:37,545
or anyone else,

563
00:45:39,825 --> 00:45:41,984
no one can make me as happy as you do.

564
00:45:50,745 --> 00:45:52,384
Why are you looking at me like that?

565
00:45:55,225 --> 00:45:56,545
I'm glad

566
00:45:56,625 --> 00:45:57,705
you are smiling.

567
00:46:01,745 --> 00:46:02,944
Sometimes, I wonder

568
00:46:03,944 --> 00:46:04,904
where you came from.

569
00:46:06,345 --> 00:46:08,025
How can you warm my heart this much?

570
00:46:14,944 --> 00:46:16,625
Your family raised you well.

571
00:46:20,505 --> 00:46:21,505
Who knows,

572
00:46:22,345 --> 00:46:24,424
maybe I came from another planet.

573
00:46:26,384 --> 00:46:27,705
Even your mom said

574
00:46:28,545 --> 00:46:30,944
I'm a Little Prince who fell from the sky.

575
00:46:32,464 --> 00:46:33,705
You can't believe her.

576
00:46:41,424 --> 00:46:43,424
Although you haven't gotten
your memory back,

577
00:46:45,424 --> 00:46:46,424
don't worry.

578
00:46:48,025 --> 00:46:49,944
I'll help you find your family.

579
00:46:54,864 --> 00:46:56,265
Will you let me stay with you

580
00:46:58,825 --> 00:47:00,665
if I don't want to leave?

581
00:47:10,225 --> 00:47:11,665
When you get your memory back,

582
00:47:13,904 --> 00:47:16,424
you might be able to get by without me.

583
00:47:31,345 --> 00:47:32,665
Don't sulk.

584
00:47:33,625 --> 00:47:34,745
I'll help you.

585
00:47:37,745 --> 00:47:39,265
I'm curious.

586
00:47:39,345 --> 00:47:40,984
If you and Tarn

587
00:47:41,065 --> 00:47:42,065
weren't an item,

588
00:47:44,745 --> 00:47:45,825
then how were you

589
00:47:47,065 --> 00:47:48,065
connected?

590
00:48:41,225 --> 00:48:43,145
If you really knew Tarn,

591
00:48:43,705 --> 00:48:44,944
maybe you came here.

592
00:48:46,785 --> 00:48:48,225
Something here

593
00:48:48,864 --> 00:48:50,305
might trigger your memory.

594
00:48:54,785 --> 00:48:55,665
Let's go inside.

595
00:49:21,984 --> 00:49:24,145
This is the first time
I'm learning about you

596
00:49:25,145 --> 00:49:26,545
from your place.

597
00:50:19,225 --> 00:50:20,384
No wonder

598
00:50:21,225 --> 00:50:23,864
you've been in Nut's heart all this time.

599
00:50:53,185 --> 00:50:54,105
Do you like it?

600
00:50:54,904 --> 00:50:56,065
It's cute.

601
00:50:59,065 --> 00:50:59,944
Like you.

602
00:51:03,625 --> 00:51:04,984
How is it like me?

603
00:51:06,665 --> 00:51:08,025
Well,

604
00:51:08,705 --> 00:51:10,305
you're covered in spines,

605
00:51:10,785 --> 00:51:12,625
always protecting yourself.

606
00:51:13,705 --> 00:51:15,424
You can endure extreme conditions,

607
00:51:16,464 --> 00:51:17,785
but deep down,

608
00:51:18,745 --> 00:51:20,825
you need someone to take care of you.

609
00:51:24,625 --> 00:51:25,665
Aren't you afraid

610
00:51:26,504 --> 00:51:27,504
of the spines?

611
00:51:28,745 --> 00:51:29,665
No.

612
00:51:30,745 --> 00:51:31,785
Despite the spines,

613
00:51:32,424 --> 00:51:33,545
you're still cute.

614
00:52:18,345 --> 00:52:19,825
When I found that photo,

615
00:52:21,665 --> 00:52:23,785
I took a picture of it,

616
00:52:23,864 --> 00:52:26,225
hoping to find Tarn's first love.

617
00:52:30,545 --> 00:52:33,825
Tarn often told me about his first love,

618
00:52:34,345 --> 00:52:36,065
but he never said who it was.

619
00:52:39,025 --> 00:52:41,545
Tarn probably didn't want to trouble you.

620
00:52:44,384 --> 00:52:46,185
It made Tarn happy

621
00:52:46,665 --> 00:52:48,665
to see you happy.

622
00:52:52,265 --> 00:52:53,225
What are you doing?

623
00:52:53,864 --> 00:52:55,745
Well, I'm taking a photo as proof.

624
00:52:56,305 --> 00:52:57,984
You promised to love me and only me.

625
00:52:58,904 --> 00:53:00,585
Stop it.

626
00:53:06,424 --> 00:53:07,345
Prib.

627
00:53:08,825 --> 00:53:10,585
Can you take me to Tarn's bedroom?

628
00:53:50,625 --> 00:53:51,825
I used to envy you.

629
00:53:52,625 --> 00:53:55,185
But I promise to envy you less.

630
00:53:56,265 --> 00:53:57,984
I want you to wake up soon.

631
00:53:59,464 --> 00:54:01,384
I can't bear seeing Nut sad anymore.

632
00:54:03,265 --> 00:54:04,785
I'm dying to know

633
00:54:05,424 --> 00:54:07,864
how a teddy bear like me
turned into a human.

634
00:54:16,545 --> 00:54:18,625
Did you say a teddy bear
turned into a human?

635
00:54:21,225 --> 00:54:22,904
Who's talking to me?

636
00:54:24,864 --> 00:54:27,944
Did a teddy bear really turn into a human?

637
00:54:31,185 --> 00:54:33,384
How is that possible?

638
00:54:33,464 --> 00:54:34,625
It's true.

639
00:54:35,705 --> 00:54:37,745
I don't know how it happened.

640
00:54:39,065 --> 00:54:41,065
I think it has something
to do with Tatarn.

641
00:54:41,944 --> 00:54:43,345
Tarn?

642
00:54:43,904 --> 00:54:44,984
Yes.

643
00:54:46,545 --> 00:54:48,785
But he can't tell me anything right now

644
00:54:50,345 --> 00:54:51,864
because he was assaulted.

645
00:54:54,585 --> 00:54:56,065
Do you happen to know

646
00:54:56,145 --> 00:54:57,585
what happened to him?

647
00:55:00,464 --> 00:55:02,424
The incident happened here.

648
00:55:03,625 --> 00:55:04,745
Here?

649
00:55:06,864 --> 00:55:08,384
Did you see the attacker?

650
00:55:08,464 --> 00:55:09,984
I didn't see anyone.

651
00:55:10,545 --> 00:55:12,225
But I heard Tatarn

652
00:55:12,305 --> 00:55:13,984
arguing with a man.

653
00:55:14,464 --> 00:55:15,864
I'm not going to back down.

654
00:55:27,864 --> 00:55:29,785
I heard a vase shatter.

655
00:55:31,864 --> 00:55:34,545
Then I heard a lot of people
coming inside the house

656
00:55:35,944 --> 00:55:37,944
before everything fell quiet.

657
00:55:41,785 --> 00:55:43,745
I don't know who they were.

658
00:55:44,464 --> 00:55:46,785
The last person who came
to clean up the scene

659
00:55:47,785 --> 00:55:49,065
missed a spot.

660
00:55:52,464 --> 00:55:53,665
What do you mean?

661
00:56:21,384 --> 00:56:22,345
It's from the vase.

662
00:56:27,705 --> 00:56:29,025
Did the attacker

663
00:56:29,105 --> 00:56:31,145
hit Tatarn in the head with the vase?

664
00:56:31,705 --> 00:56:33,625
I'm not sure.

665
00:56:33,705 --> 00:56:36,864
But I'm certain that the last person

666
00:56:37,464 --> 00:56:38,864
who came inside

667
00:56:38,944 --> 00:56:40,384
was a woman.

668
00:56:43,265 --> 00:56:44,145
A woman?

669
00:56:45,105 --> 00:56:47,464
Is anyone inside the house?
Come out this instant.

670
00:56:50,065 --> 00:56:51,625
It's her.

671
00:56:51,705 --> 00:56:52,665
It was her voice.

672
00:56:53,944 --> 00:56:54,864
What did you say?

673
00:56:58,424 --> 00:56:59,464
You…

674
00:56:59,545 --> 00:57:00,944
What are you doing here?

675
00:57:01,024 --> 00:57:02,345
Who gave you permission?

676
00:57:04,464 --> 00:57:05,825
I did.

677
00:57:07,745 --> 00:57:08,825
Saen.

678
00:57:13,545 --> 00:57:14,665
Thank you for letting me

679
00:57:15,984 --> 00:57:17,705
bring Tofu here, Uncle Saen.

680
00:57:18,705 --> 00:57:19,825
You are welcome.

681
00:57:20,384 --> 00:57:21,625
Mr. Anik called me.

682
00:57:22,864 --> 00:57:24,504
It's a shame we can't help Tofu.

683
00:57:25,105 --> 00:57:27,185
There's no link between Tofu and Tatarn.

684
00:57:27,944 --> 00:57:28,984
You made up a theory

685
00:57:29,065 --> 00:57:30,984
and came to search someone's house

686
00:57:31,065 --> 00:57:33,105
when the owner's relative
doesn't welcome you.

687
00:57:33,745 --> 00:57:35,185
Why don't you want us here?

688
00:57:35,944 --> 00:57:37,145
This house is beautiful.

689
00:57:38,145 --> 00:57:40,065
Are you hiding something from us?

690
00:57:43,864 --> 00:57:46,825
This house is full of expensive artwork.

691
00:57:46,904 --> 00:57:48,864
I'm Tarn's only relative.

692
00:57:48,944 --> 00:57:50,145
With him in the hospital,

693
00:57:50,225 --> 00:57:52,265
Saen and I need
to watch this house for him.

694
00:57:52,345 --> 00:57:55,065
I will be held responsible
if anything goes missing.

695
00:57:57,545 --> 00:57:58,904
Did you agree to look after it

696
00:57:59,545 --> 00:58:00,625
to offer help

697
00:58:01,585 --> 00:58:02,944
or for something in return?

698
00:58:04,065 --> 00:58:05,384
Nut.

699
00:58:06,665 --> 00:58:08,024
Isn't your mom at the hotel?

700
00:58:08,944 --> 00:58:10,065
You should check on her.

701
00:58:10,145 --> 00:58:11,345
I'll lock up the house.

702
00:58:11,424 --> 00:58:12,944
We should go

703
00:58:13,024 --> 00:58:14,585
before something goes missing.

704
00:58:15,305 --> 00:58:16,585
Hey.

705
00:58:17,705 --> 00:58:19,305
-Listen to her.
-Stop.

706
00:58:23,665 --> 00:58:25,024
Teddy.

707
00:58:26,105 --> 00:58:28,944
The voices I heard that day

708
00:58:29,024 --> 00:58:30,745
belong to these two people.

709
00:58:34,065 --> 00:58:37,024
You must find Tarn's attackers.

710
00:59:01,705 --> 00:59:03,625
How could you let them inside the house?

711
00:59:04,705 --> 00:59:05,705
I had no choice.

712
00:59:06,185 --> 00:59:07,984
The officer called to ask for a favor.

713
00:59:08,065 --> 00:59:09,705
I couldn't trigger his suspicion.

714
00:59:09,785 --> 00:59:12,625
Did you see the way
they were looking at us?

715
00:59:13,145 --> 00:59:14,024
Do you really think

716
00:59:14,105 --> 00:59:16,504
they came here to get Tofu's memory back?

717
00:59:38,625 --> 00:59:41,625
TATARN KLAIANANT

718
00:59:41,705 --> 00:59:45,745
AN ARTIST WHOSE VOICE IS HEARD THROUGH ART

719
00:59:46,825 --> 00:59:48,464
Tarn, the guy Tofu recognized,

720
00:59:49,105 --> 00:59:50,185
is Jan's nephew.

721
00:59:51,665 --> 00:59:52,825
My name is Tatarn.

722
00:59:53,545 --> 00:59:55,065
I just came back from Japan.

723
00:59:56,105 --> 00:59:57,105
Tatarn…

724
01:00:10,145 --> 01:00:11,024
Mom.

725
01:00:12,625 --> 01:00:13,625
Is something wrong?

726
01:00:20,225 --> 01:00:21,185
No.

727
01:00:25,665 --> 01:00:26,665
Are you free later?

728
01:00:29,065 --> 01:00:30,185
Where do you want to go?

729
01:00:31,145 --> 01:00:32,384
I want to visit him.

730
01:01:13,585 --> 01:01:14,705
Who are you here to see?

731
01:01:14,785 --> 01:01:16,024
Hello.

732
01:01:17,384 --> 01:01:18,665
I'm here to see Nut.

733
01:01:21,545 --> 01:01:22,665
-Thank you.
-No problem.

734
01:01:26,345 --> 01:01:27,984
It's a shame Nut is out of town.

735
01:01:29,065 --> 01:01:30,705
You came here for nothing.

736
01:01:30,785 --> 01:01:32,065
It's fine.

737
01:01:32,665 --> 01:01:34,904
I thought you were my student.

738
01:01:35,825 --> 01:01:37,105
Are you Nut's friend?

739
01:01:37,185 --> 01:01:38,625
Yes.

740
01:01:39,185 --> 01:01:40,745
What's your name?

741
01:01:43,984 --> 01:01:44,825
My name is Tatarn.

742
01:01:46,065 --> 01:01:47,265
I've returned from Japan.

743
01:01:47,345 --> 01:01:49,265
I heard Nut moved here.

744
01:01:49,345 --> 01:01:51,424
I have something to give him.

745
01:01:54,864 --> 01:01:55,705
Here it is.

746
01:01:57,145 --> 01:01:57,984
I drew it myself.

747
01:01:58,065 --> 01:01:59,345
-Really?
-Yes.

748
01:02:07,305 --> 01:02:09,185
Wow, it's adorable.

749
01:02:11,665 --> 01:02:14,864
IT'S NICE TO HAVE SOMEONE BY YOUR SIDE

750
01:02:15,625 --> 01:02:18,825
"It's nice to have someone by your side."

751
01:02:21,065 --> 01:02:21,904
Right, honey?

752
01:02:27,185 --> 01:02:29,345
I'll give this to Nut

753
01:02:29,424 --> 01:02:30,504
when he returns.

754
01:02:31,785 --> 01:02:32,825
Thank you so much.

755
01:02:37,105 --> 01:02:38,024
By the way,

756
01:02:38,705 --> 01:02:40,265
are you here alone?

757
01:02:40,345 --> 01:02:42,065
What are you talking about?

758
01:02:42,145 --> 01:02:44,904
I'm here with Nut's father

759
01:02:44,984 --> 01:02:46,705
and Kuenchai.

760
01:02:54,745 --> 01:02:55,864
Nut's father?

761
01:03:02,305 --> 01:03:03,185
Mom.

762
01:03:05,225 --> 01:03:07,105
Why did you want to see Tarn?

763
01:03:11,424 --> 01:03:12,984
He came to our house.

764
01:03:18,265 --> 01:03:19,265
When?

765
01:03:24,545 --> 01:03:26,024
I don't remember.

766
01:03:27,864 --> 01:03:29,944
But it was after we moved
to the new house.

767
01:03:33,585 --> 01:03:34,984
He brought

768
01:03:36,305 --> 01:03:37,225
the book…

769
01:03:40,424 --> 01:03:41,625
Your favorite book.

770
01:03:43,745 --> 01:03:44,785
He brought it for you.

771
01:03:49,065 --> 01:03:50,105
Kuenchai.

772
01:03:50,665 --> 01:03:52,384
I've got snacks.

773
01:03:52,464 --> 01:03:53,745
Do you want some?

774
01:03:53,825 --> 01:03:55,065
Do you want some? Come.

775
01:03:55,904 --> 01:03:57,145
Show me a jump.

776
01:03:57,225 --> 01:03:58,145
Jump for me.

777
01:03:58,785 --> 01:04:00,705
Jump!

778
01:04:00,785 --> 01:04:01,785
Jump! Oh, no.

779
01:04:01,864 --> 01:04:03,384
-No.
-Hey.

780
01:04:03,464 --> 01:04:04,305
-Oh, no.
-Gosh.

781
01:04:05,424 --> 01:04:06,625
That was a pounce. Oops.

782
01:04:32,265 --> 01:04:33,424
Is this your book?

783
01:04:34,265 --> 01:04:35,105
What?

784
01:04:35,785 --> 01:04:36,785
It's yours.

785
01:04:38,585 --> 01:04:39,825
This isn't mine.

786
01:04:40,785 --> 01:04:42,185
It's yours.

787
01:04:42,984 --> 01:04:44,105
You should put it away.

788
01:05:06,745 --> 01:05:08,705
THE PERSON WHO ALWAYS LOOKS AT YOU

789
01:05:11,024 --> 01:05:12,024
THANK YOU

790
01:05:12,105 --> 01:05:15,065
EVERY DAY WITH YOU

791
01:05:15,145 --> 01:05:19,944
I'VE NEVER FORGOTTEN OUR DAYS TOGETHER

792
01:05:20,024 --> 01:05:24,464
THANK YOU

793
01:05:45,265 --> 01:05:47,625
Tarn brought me that book.

794
01:05:48,424 --> 01:05:50,145
Why didn't you tell me?

795
01:05:52,225 --> 01:05:54,225
You always forget the important stuff.

796
01:05:58,145 --> 01:05:59,265
I've been sick.

797
01:06:01,345 --> 01:06:03,345
I don't remember who gave you the book.

798
01:06:08,265 --> 01:06:11,424
You weren't around much back then,
so I forgot.

799
01:06:14,024 --> 01:06:15,225
I'm sorry.

800
01:06:16,065 --> 01:06:17,065
Nut.

801
01:06:20,904 --> 01:06:22,265
If you leave now,

802
01:06:23,585 --> 01:06:25,225
you'll hurt her feelings.

803
01:06:28,105 --> 01:06:29,745
Don't you think I'm hurt too?

804
01:06:34,625 --> 01:06:35,904
I know you're hurt as well.

805
01:06:51,785 --> 01:06:52,705
You should know

806
01:06:53,185 --> 01:06:54,864
how disappointed,

807
01:06:54,944 --> 01:06:55,984
sad,

808
01:06:56,065 --> 01:06:56,984
and upset I am.

809
01:06:59,625 --> 01:07:01,745
But I'm angrier at my fate than my mom.

810
01:07:03,345 --> 01:07:05,225
How would my life be like

811
01:07:06,225 --> 01:07:07,145
if she had told me?

812
01:07:09,225 --> 01:07:10,864
Nut would be really happy

813
01:07:12,785 --> 01:07:15,225
to have Tatarn next to him now,

814
01:07:17,225 --> 01:07:18,185
instead of me.

815
01:07:19,665 --> 01:07:21,464
No one knows

816
01:07:21,544 --> 01:07:23,464
whether you would be happy or sad.

817
01:07:24,185 --> 01:07:25,504
You might think

818
01:07:25,585 --> 01:07:27,384
that you guys would be together now.

819
01:07:28,024 --> 01:07:29,145
But don't forget

820
01:07:29,225 --> 01:07:31,145
your mom was sick,
and she was conservative

821
01:07:31,745 --> 01:07:32,864
two years ago.

822
01:07:33,345 --> 01:07:35,625
Your relationship with Tarn
would be a secret

823
01:07:35,705 --> 01:07:37,745
unlike your relationship with Tofu now.

824
01:07:40,384 --> 01:07:41,345
Tofu.

825
01:07:42,065 --> 01:07:45,105
Everything requires good timing.

826
01:07:46,024 --> 01:07:47,464
Two years ago,

827
01:07:47,544 --> 01:07:49,145
Tarn's timing was wrong.

828
01:07:49,225 --> 01:07:50,464
That's why they broke up.

829
01:07:52,464 --> 01:07:53,745
On the other hand,

830
01:07:53,825 --> 01:07:56,145
you walked into Nut's life
at the perfect time.

831
01:07:58,705 --> 01:08:00,705
But Tatarn is back in the picture now.

832
01:08:03,024 --> 01:08:05,504
Is it possible that
this is the right timing

833
01:08:07,585 --> 01:08:08,745
for them to reunite?

834
01:08:10,544 --> 01:08:12,185
Being afraid of the future

835
01:08:12,265 --> 01:08:15,745
is as bad as wanting to fix the past.

836
01:08:16,305 --> 01:08:17,305
You should live

837
01:08:18,265 --> 01:08:19,504
in the present.

838
01:08:20,105 --> 01:08:23,305
You should use the time to worry
about your loved ones' feelings.

839
01:08:24,105 --> 01:08:25,504
You are confusing Tofu

840
01:08:26,225 --> 01:08:29,305
by expressing countless concerns
toward your ex-boyfriend.

841
01:08:52,905 --> 01:08:53,905
I was looking for you.

842
01:08:56,185 --> 01:08:57,584
Me too.

843
01:09:00,544 --> 01:09:01,865
I know

844
01:09:01,945 --> 01:09:03,384
it's hard to accept

845
01:09:04,464 --> 01:09:06,624
that you had almost crossed paths with him

846
01:09:08,065 --> 01:09:09,985
and could have gotten back together,

847
01:09:12,145 --> 01:09:14,145
but your sick mom took away the chance.

848
01:09:16,985 --> 01:09:18,345
I don't mind the situation.

849
01:09:19,945 --> 01:09:21,225
I'm just regretful.

850
01:09:22,105 --> 01:09:23,624
If I had met him back then,

851
01:09:24,384 --> 01:09:25,744
I could have apologized.

852
01:09:27,464 --> 01:09:28,384
But now,

853
01:09:29,544 --> 01:09:31,384
I might not get a chance to apologize.

854
01:09:32,784 --> 01:09:34,384
He might not wake up

855
01:09:36,865 --> 01:09:38,424
to watch the series I produced.

856
01:09:41,825 --> 01:09:43,744
I'm sure he's going to wake up.

857
01:09:45,065 --> 01:09:46,664
You worked really hard on it.

858
01:09:47,664 --> 01:09:48,744
Who knows,

859
01:09:49,664 --> 01:09:51,945
a miracle might happen.

860
01:09:58,265 --> 01:09:59,225
Give me a hug.

861
01:10:09,425 --> 01:10:10,305
Are you hungry?

862
01:10:11,465 --> 01:10:12,704
My stomach didn't growl.

863
01:10:13,385 --> 01:10:14,345
It wasn't mine.

864
01:10:18,145 --> 01:10:19,425
It was mine.

865
01:10:20,385 --> 01:10:22,065
-You.
-Hey.

866
01:10:22,145 --> 01:10:24,945
Your stomach growled really loud.
Why don't you eat something?

867
01:10:25,025 --> 01:10:26,345
Wait.

868
01:10:26,425 --> 01:10:28,664
Didn't we just eat?

869
01:10:30,664 --> 01:10:33,585
It took a lot of energy to get them

870
01:10:33,664 --> 01:10:35,345
to make up.

871
01:10:36,505 --> 01:10:37,905
Shall we go eat?

872
01:10:38,825 --> 01:10:39,744
-Yes.
-Let's go.

873
01:10:45,065 --> 01:10:46,105
Let me get my mom.

874
01:10:46,185 --> 01:10:48,145
This meal is on Nut then.

875
01:10:48,225 --> 01:10:51,265
He made up with his boyfriend after all.

876
01:10:51,345 --> 01:10:53,585
-Yes!
-Yes!

877
01:10:53,664 --> 01:10:55,065
Yes!

878
01:10:55,825 --> 01:10:57,105
-Let's go, Tofu.
-All right.

879
01:10:57,784 --> 01:10:59,945
We're getting a free meal. Let's go.

880
01:11:00,465 --> 01:11:01,624
Come on.

881
01:11:09,985 --> 01:11:10,865
Mom.

882
01:11:12,624 --> 01:11:13,585
Mom.

883
01:11:14,265 --> 01:11:15,225
Let's grab some food.

884
01:11:17,465 --> 01:11:18,385
Mrs. Na.

885
01:11:22,345 --> 01:11:23,225
Mom.

886
01:11:27,025 --> 01:11:27,865
Mom.

887
01:11:28,385 --> 01:11:29,585
Let's eat.

888
01:11:29,664 --> 01:11:30,624
Mrs. Na.

889
01:11:37,025 --> 01:11:37,865
Mom.

890
01:11:38,465 --> 01:11:39,425
Mrs. Na.

891
01:11:43,744 --> 01:11:44,664
Mom.

892
01:11:48,305 --> 01:11:49,225
Mom.

893
01:11:51,905 --> 01:11:52,825
Nut.

894
01:12:21,345 --> 01:12:23,185
-Gen, have you seen my mom?
-What?

895
01:12:23,265 --> 01:12:24,945
-Your mom?
-She's missing.

896
01:12:26,825 --> 01:12:28,145
Nut.

897
01:12:31,145 --> 01:12:31,985
Nut.

898
01:12:32,585 --> 01:12:34,105
-I'll check the front.
-Okay.

899
01:12:34,185 --> 01:12:35,065
See you.

900
01:12:35,145 --> 01:12:36,305
-Excuse me.
-Yes.

901
01:12:36,385 --> 01:12:38,145
Have you seen the guest from Room 202?

902
01:12:38,225 --> 01:12:39,744
She's tall and thin.

903
01:12:39,825 --> 01:12:40,985
Around 50 years old.

904
01:12:41,545 --> 01:12:43,744
She's wearing a blue shirt
with grey pants.

905
01:12:44,704 --> 01:12:47,305
Yes, she left the hotel
about half an hour ago.

906
01:12:47,385 --> 01:12:48,945
Can we help you with anything?

907
01:12:50,065 --> 01:12:51,945
Can you check the security footage?

908
01:12:52,025 --> 01:12:52,985
Of course.

909
01:13:05,225 --> 01:13:06,225
How did it go?

910
01:13:06,305 --> 01:13:08,065
She walked out by herself

911
01:13:08,145 --> 01:13:09,545
without her wallet or phone.

912
01:13:10,825 --> 01:13:12,185
Where did she go?

913
01:13:13,545 --> 01:13:16,265
Maybe she's taking a walk.

914
01:13:18,624 --> 01:13:20,185
Is she that mad at me?

915
01:13:20,265 --> 01:13:22,784
Maybe she wants to be alone
to think things over.

916
01:13:22,865 --> 01:13:24,465
Calm down.

917
01:13:25,025 --> 01:13:26,744
How about we look for her?

918
01:13:27,425 --> 01:13:28,784
I told the hotel to call us

919
01:13:28,865 --> 01:13:30,385
if she comes back.

920
01:13:31,265 --> 01:13:32,664
She just left.

921
01:13:32,744 --> 01:13:34,185
She couldn't have gone far.

922
01:13:34,265 --> 01:13:37,065
We should look for her in the city.

923
01:13:38,145 --> 01:13:38,985
Let's go.

924
01:13:39,065 --> 01:13:40,305
Come on.

925
01:13:40,385 --> 01:13:41,225
Come, Tofu.

926
01:16:09,744 --> 01:16:10,624
Excuse me.

927
01:16:11,225 --> 01:16:12,545
Have you seen this woman?

928
01:16:13,945 --> 01:16:16,265
Yes, I saw her near the river.

929
01:16:17,585 --> 01:16:18,505
Thank you.

930
01:16:18,585 --> 01:16:19,425
Let's go, Tofu.

931
01:16:47,385 --> 01:16:48,465
-Mom.
-Mrs. Na.

932
01:16:51,025 --> 01:16:51,985
I'm sorry.

933
01:16:57,545 --> 01:16:58,545
Let's keep going.

934
01:17:31,385 --> 01:17:32,505
Excuse me.

935
01:17:32,585 --> 01:17:33,664
I…

936
01:17:34,225 --> 01:17:35,145
How can I help you?

937
01:17:36,545 --> 01:17:38,545
I want to go to…

938
01:17:40,425 --> 01:17:41,425
Where are you going?

939
01:17:47,585 --> 01:17:49,824
Are you here alone?

940
01:17:51,824 --> 01:17:54,185
Why don't you call a relative
to pick you up?

941
01:17:54,784 --> 01:17:56,545
I didn't bring my phone.

942
01:17:57,664 --> 01:17:58,824
In that case,

943
01:17:58,905 --> 01:18:00,624
shall I take you home?

944
01:18:00,704 --> 01:18:02,025
Where do you live?

945
01:18:09,824 --> 01:18:13,465
Someone brought her here
after finding her near the river.

946
01:18:13,985 --> 01:18:16,865
She said she's here
with her son named Nut and Tofu.

947
01:18:17,425 --> 01:18:18,985
I thought of you.

948
01:18:20,105 --> 01:18:22,385
I totally forgot about you.

949
01:18:23,225 --> 01:18:24,624
Unbelievable.

950
01:18:24,704 --> 01:18:26,865
You didn't think of your father
who's a cop.

951
01:18:26,945 --> 01:18:28,545
I didn't know

952
01:18:28,624 --> 01:18:30,545
he was your father.

953
01:18:30,624 --> 01:18:33,425
It's such a small world.

954
01:18:35,145 --> 01:18:36,025
Mom.

955
01:18:36,505 --> 01:18:38,065
How did you end up there?

956
01:18:42,905 --> 01:18:43,824
Nut.

957
01:18:44,585 --> 01:18:46,545
Why don't we talk at the hotel?

958
01:18:51,824 --> 01:18:52,664
Nut.

959
01:18:53,545 --> 01:18:54,425
Can we talk?

960
01:19:20,505 --> 01:19:22,025
Your mom said

961
01:19:22,824 --> 01:19:24,265
she suddenly lost her memory

962
01:19:25,025 --> 01:19:26,345
while taking a walk.

963
01:19:27,425 --> 01:19:30,065
She forgot where she was,
so she kept walking.

964
01:19:31,505 --> 01:19:34,985
The person who found her
also said she seemed strange.

965
01:19:35,065 --> 01:19:36,345
She sounded confused.

966
01:19:37,225 --> 01:19:38,824
She couldn't answer her.

967
01:19:40,185 --> 01:19:42,065
I think something is wrong with her.

968
01:19:43,744 --> 01:19:46,465
You should talk to your mom
to see what the problem is.

969
01:19:51,425 --> 01:19:52,545
I will, sir.

970
01:19:53,185 --> 01:19:54,025
Thank you so much.

971
01:20:03,945 --> 01:20:05,025
The reason you left…

972
01:20:07,345 --> 01:20:08,425
you weren't mad, right?

973
01:20:11,465 --> 01:20:12,985
Was there another reason?

974
01:20:54,105 --> 01:20:55,664
How long has this been happening?

975
01:21:04,945 --> 01:21:06,345
I don't know.

976
01:21:12,265 --> 01:21:14,465
I feel strange.

977
01:21:21,305 --> 01:21:22,265
I…

978
01:21:23,425 --> 01:21:25,545
I'm getting very forgetful, Nut.

979
01:21:31,225 --> 01:21:32,585
I forget…

980
01:21:35,345 --> 01:21:36,385
what I'm going to do.

981
01:21:39,985 --> 01:21:41,465
I forget

982
01:21:42,465 --> 01:21:43,945
what I've done.

983
01:21:48,744 --> 01:21:49,945
I forget days.

984
01:21:54,065 --> 01:21:55,385
I forget people's names.

985
01:21:57,345 --> 01:21:59,025
Sometimes, I forget

986
01:22:01,185 --> 01:22:02,865
what I want to say.

987
01:22:11,905 --> 01:22:13,385
I went to see the doctor.

988
01:22:16,265 --> 01:22:18,744
Dr. Kanya examined me.

989
01:22:25,145 --> 01:22:27,505
She said…

990
01:22:30,784 --> 01:22:32,225
I'm showing symptoms of…

991
01:22:35,265 --> 01:22:36,185
Alzheimer's.

992
01:22:45,105 --> 01:22:46,465
I'm sorry, Nut.

993
01:22:52,744 --> 01:22:53,784
It's okay, Mom.

994
01:24:02,225 --> 01:24:04,704
The truth is she has been
showing signs for a while.

995
01:24:07,265 --> 01:24:08,744
I didn't think much of them.

996
01:24:11,905 --> 01:24:12,905
These three, please.

997
01:24:14,865 --> 01:24:16,704
Didn't I just buy some last week?

998
01:24:17,425 --> 01:24:18,465
Why have we run out?

999
01:24:20,265 --> 01:24:22,585
Your mom has been feeding Kuenchai
a lot more often.

1000
01:24:23,065 --> 01:24:24,784
Some days she feeds him several times.

1001
01:24:30,225 --> 01:24:31,865
I'm a horrible son.

1002
01:24:46,905 --> 01:24:48,385
You've been working hard.

1003
01:24:50,185 --> 01:24:51,985
You've got a lot on your mind.

1004
01:24:54,465 --> 01:24:55,664
On the other hand,

1005
01:24:57,585 --> 01:24:59,225
it's my job to take care of her.

1006
01:25:01,664 --> 01:25:03,345
I've been with her the whole time.

1007
01:25:05,945 --> 01:25:07,664
I saw her abnormalities.

1008
01:25:16,345 --> 01:25:18,025
Did I already feed you?

1009
01:25:20,025 --> 01:25:21,865
Kuenchai, come and eat.

1010
01:25:25,425 --> 01:25:26,865
You already gave him his food.

1011
01:25:28,145 --> 01:25:29,385
Did I?

1012
01:25:39,425 --> 01:25:40,865
Are you looking for something?

1013
01:25:40,945 --> 01:25:42,784
I'm looking for the fruit knife.

1014
01:25:43,824 --> 01:25:45,545
I don't know where I put it.

1015
01:25:58,425 --> 01:26:00,225
I didn't suspect a thing.

1016
01:26:06,105 --> 01:26:07,505
I'm sorry, Nut.

1017
01:26:10,545 --> 01:26:12,025
Why is this happening?

1018
01:26:15,065 --> 01:26:16,744
Everything was getting better.

1019
01:26:19,265 --> 01:26:21,145
Our family was about to be happy.

1020
01:26:24,704 --> 01:26:26,225
Don't I deserve

1021
01:26:28,065 --> 01:26:29,585
to be happy?

1022
01:26:42,465 --> 01:26:43,945
Don't blame yourself.

1023
01:26:46,545 --> 01:26:48,225
No one is to blame here.

1024
01:26:52,744 --> 01:26:54,744
Since your mom is already sick,

1025
01:26:57,624 --> 01:27:00,065
why don't we find a way to help her?

1026
01:27:05,545 --> 01:27:06,864
This disease

1027
01:27:06,945 --> 01:27:08,385
can't be cured.

1028
01:27:10,824 --> 01:27:11,985
Soon…

1029
01:27:14,425 --> 01:27:15,824
she will forget you,

1030
01:27:18,065 --> 01:27:19,265
me,

1031
01:27:22,624 --> 01:27:24,185
and even herself.

1032
01:27:41,305 --> 01:27:42,945
Let's come up with a way

1033
01:27:45,505 --> 01:27:47,265
to take care of her

1034
01:27:50,305 --> 01:27:52,185
before she forgets everything.

1035
01:28:09,744 --> 01:28:10,824
Who do you suspect?

1036
01:28:10,905 --> 01:28:12,185
Tofu.

1037
01:28:12,265 --> 01:28:15,664
He could have been in the house that day
and saw the whole thing.

1038
01:28:16,265 --> 01:28:19,704
If you don't want
a twisted, tormented life like mine,

1039
01:28:20,185 --> 01:28:22,025
you'll have to live mindfully.

1040
01:28:23,265 --> 01:28:25,385
Correct your mistakes while you still can.

1041
01:28:26,025 --> 01:28:27,545
One person lost his memory.

1042
01:28:28,704 --> 01:28:30,105
Another person is losing hers.

1043
01:28:32,265 --> 01:28:33,265
Who knows?

1044
01:28:34,025 --> 01:28:36,105
I might remember something soon.

1045
01:28:39,385 --> 01:28:41,385
You've been doing a great job.

1046
01:28:45,585 --> 01:28:46,664
Don't blame yourself.

1047
01:28:49,744 --> 01:28:50,704
You did great.

